Collapses factor levels and returns a new data frame

Source: R/utils.R
collapse_cats.Rd

This function is a wrapper around forcats::fct_collapse(). It takes a dataframe, a factor variable, and a list of factor levels to collapse.

Usage

collapse_cats(data, item, collaps_cats)

Arguments

data

dataset

item

factor variable

collaps_cats

list of factor levels to collapse in shape of list(new_level = old_level)

Value

new data frame with collapsed factor levels

Examples

collapse_cats(trust, police, list(Agree = c("Definitely Agree", "Rather Agree")))
